# Files excluded from semgrep scans. Paths relative to repo root.
#
# Rule of thumb: list directories that ship upstream-owned C/C++/Python we
# don't author or modify — semgrep findings there would be noise we can't
# act on without diverging from upstream.

# Netflix-upstream MATLAB MEX helpers. Pure research reference, not linked
# into libvmaf. The MEX sources use sprintf() in mexErrMsgTxt calls and
# match our CERT STR31-C guard rule (vmaf-no-strcpy-strcat-sprintf).
python/vmaf/matlab/

# Netflix-upstream Python training resource tree (datasets, param/feature
# dicts). Not C/C++; included here for completeness since semgrep's Python
# rules could fire on the same upstream drift ruff is silenced on.
python/vmaf/resource/

# Standard exclusions — third-party / generated.
subprojects/
build/
dist/
libvmaf/test/data/
model/
testdata/

